        Retrieves all requested information on two location points. During the retrieval, this class also takes predefined request settings into consideration As stated before (in the beginning of this document, you need one API-key from Google API Console (https://code.google.com/apis/console). After passing your API-key to this method, GeocodingApi fetches the latitude and longitude values of both the origin address, and the destination address. These values are evaluated by DistanceMatrixApi in order to calculate the distance between two location points, and how long it takes to get from one location point to another. In addition, ElevationApi calculates the elevation value. This value might be interesting for mountaineers, and strollers who like go for a walk in a forest.
